<paragraph blockId="22.[151,756,466,586]" pageId="22" pageNumber="97">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,283,466,489]" pageId="22" pageNumber="97">Comments:</emphasis>
The species shares many aedeagal characters with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lobl" authorityYear="2015" box="[259,402,498,521]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scaphisoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adjunctum">
<emphasis box="[259,402,498,521]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="97">S. adjunctum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It may be easily distinguished from the latter by the larger body size, colour and punctation of the elytra, and by the shape of the parameres.
</paragraph>
